LOCUS       Gateway_attB2             25 bp    DNA              UNK 01-JAN-1980
DEFINITION  Gateway attB2 minimal attachment site; 25 bp, the specificity-2 attB
            recombination site appended to a DNA fragment through the attB2 PCR
            primer tail. It recombines with attP2 (BP reaction) to move the
            fragment into a pDONR entry vector. An engineered lambda-derived
            site; the canonical sequence is from Hartley, Temple & Brasch 2000..
ACCESSION   Gateway_attB2
VERSION     Gateway_attB2
